### Personal Financial Tracker API — manual request collection
### Requires the "REST Client" extension (VS Code/Cursor) or a JetBrains IDE's
### built-in HTTP client. Run `npm run dev` first, then click "Send Request"
### above any request below. New endpoints should get a request here as they
### land, so this file stays a live, runnable map of the API surface.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### Health check — confirms the server is up
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### Auth: current session (expect 200 + null body when logged out)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/get-session

### Auth: register via Better Auth's own endpoint (autoSignIn: false — no session is created)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-up/email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "manual-test@example.com",
  "password": "testpassword123",
  "name": "Manual Test"
}

### Auth: same email again — should return the same 200 shape (enumeration protection).
### Check the DB directly (see docs/DECISIONS.md) to confirm no second row was created.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-up/email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "manual-test@example.com",
  "password": "testpassword123",
  "name": "Manual Test"
}

### Sanity check: a genuinely unmounted path should still 404 (mount is scoped, not catch-all)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/totally-made-up-path

### Auth: sign-in (wrong password on purpose). Click "Send Request" 6x within
### 60s — the first 5 should return 401, the 6th should return 429
### (customRules rate limit on /sign-in/email, see docs/DECISIONS.md).
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-in/email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "ratelimit-test@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword123"
}
